# Metadata for 98-APR-3
**Original location:** `More My Documents/98/98-APR-3`
**Date:** 1998
**Full date:** 1998-04-28
**Date confidence:** high
**Date source:** Internal document: "I begin this modified version of <wp\98\98-apr-1> on April 28"

**Category:** essay-draft language searle speech-acts derrida kant faith practical-understanding

**Abstract:**
Revised version of "On Written and Spoken Language" dated April 28, 1998. Opens with Kant's definition of faith and Adorno on rhetoric. Develops detailed critique of Searle's speech-act theory, arguing he confuses philosophical reflection on language with actual linguistic commerce. Introduces concept of "practical understanding" distinct from Searle's speculative understanding. Argues statements aim at conduct-in-response, not mere understanding. Critiques deconstructionists for applying their critique only to written texts.

**AI Recommendation:** Revised version of 98-APR-1; more developed critique of Searle.

